The paper focuses on using live data from a robotic surgical system to improve the accuracy of Finite Element Method (FEM) simulations for soft-tissue deformation. This involves both vision (using point cloud data) and kinematics (using robot arm movement data) information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques to predict correction factors, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
